𝗟𝗲𝘁’𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝘂𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗜𝗡𝗘𝗤𝗨𝗔𝗟𝗜𝗧𝗬 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗴𝗲𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗲𝗾𝘂𝗮𝗹. 𝗔𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘀𝗲𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗲𝘁 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗖𝗧𝗥𝗟 + 𝗛𝗔𝗖𝗞 + 𝗗𝗘𝗟 𝗜𝗡𝗘𝗤𝗨𝗔𝗟𝗜𝗧𝗬 ?🧐

As 𝗔𝗰𝗰𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 celebrates yet another successful year of equality lead innovation, its commitment to equality for all has never been more relevant than it is today – the past year has inspired us to drive our innovation agenda and act as responsible business leaders. And what makes it even more exciting is that this time we are coding for EQUALITY, hacking our way into a stronger, and inclusive work culture. 🤩💪🏻🌈


𝗥𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱 1⃣:
By 10 PM on 1st April, team leaders will receive a coding test link on their registered email ID. Teams will have to solve two coding questions in 3 hours. This test can be taken up between 2nd April 2021 – 4th April 2021. This challenge needs to be taken up as a team. You can share your screen in a meeting call (or any other medium) and solve it together.


𝗥𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱 2⃣:
In the second coding round, teams will solve two more coding questions in 3 hours of a higher complexity.

The contest will be conducted in two rounds scheduled over two consecutive weekends. The cumulative scores from tests in both rounds will be used to decide the winners.



🔺 𝗘𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗶𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆:

This contest is open to all the students from all the engineering colleges in India.


🔺𝗧𝗲𝗮𝗺 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻:

✅ Register for the challenge and form teams of 1-4 members. Participants can form teams with students from the same college only.


✅ We believe in gender equality and therefore, we would ask the teams to be gender-balanced in terms of participants. Teams with equal gender representation will be given one additional bonus point. 


𝙏𝙤𝙥 3 𝙬𝙞𝙣𝙣𝙚𝙧𝙨 𝙬𝙞𝙡𝙡 𝙗𝙚 𝙖𝙬𝙖𝙧𝙙𝙚𝙙 🏆💰🪙


🗓️ 𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲: 1st April 2021 (6 PM)


